The President of the United States, Joseph R. Biden, and the President of the Council of Ministers of the Italian Republic, Giorgia Meloni, met at the White House to reaffirm the strong alliance and partnership between the two countries. They emphasized the shared values of democracy, freedom, and respect for human rights. The leaders discussed various global issues, including the conflict in Ukraine and the need to address its consequences, stability in the Mediterranean region, support for the Western Balkans' integration, cooperation in the Indo-Pacific region, and promoting global prosperity and peace through multilateral efforts. They also highlighted the importance of cybersecurity, emerging technologies, economic cooperation, climate change, space exploration, and collaboration in science and education. The meeting aimed to strengthen bilateral ties and address common challenges facing the international community.